PublicProfile?language=EN>MtYermom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/4/02 9:21:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=473.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Success!</span><hr size=1> I kited those wonderful lil' gobbies over and over again last night, got a lvl before I finally had to pass out.  WHAT A RUSH!!  I've found a new passion!  Going back for more now...<br><br><br><br>Raelar Arcanus<br>28th level wizard on Bertox<br>Quad Kiter (at last) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unoslomt1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoslomT1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/6/02 7:06:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=473.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Success!</span><hr size=1> Grats !  It does get the ol blood pumping doesnt it.  Seeing 4 exp messages fly bye is great <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>Wait till you get into an AoE group and get so many exp messages at once they blur on the screen and give you a touch of lag <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR>Noslom Tallone55th High Elven Shok'gun</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unoslomt1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoslomT1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/6/02 7:07:54 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneilyxdawizofoz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neilyx DaWizofOz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/6/02 3:13:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=473.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Grats</span><hr size=1> Quadding is one of the greatest things a wizzy can do. The overall risk vs. reward equals out to an insane good , andrenaline-pounding time. <br>I first quaddung in velios, but have pushed every wizard and druid in my guild to give it a try.<br><br>I quad whenever I need to level quickly, and group with guildies for the companionship.<br><br>Wait until you snare yourself my accident that first time...(lol)<br><br>Neilyx DaWizofOz<br>52 Channeler <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugarrathmoore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garrath Moore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/12/02 11:13:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=473.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats</span><hr size=1> Nelyix,<br><br>The very first time I tried to quad I snared myself and got annhiliated...thanks for reopening that old wound lol<br><br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>-G <p>Garrath Moore <BR>Wizard of the 48th Quad<BR>Officer, Divine Fate <BR>Ayonae Ro <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujather.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/21/02 6:45:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=473.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats</span><hr size=1> Almost happended to me once but I resisted it....with only 25 MR go figure... <p>Jather BlazingSoul<Br>35th and climbing wizard of E'ci<Br><a target="new" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=293498>My_Magelo</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uimprezaphreak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImprezaPhreak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/25/02 8:03:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=473.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats</span><hr size=1> Yes thanks for reminding me how horrible my first days learning to kite felt <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I think I snared my self at least 3 times and even rooted myself once or twice and just got beat to a messy gob of goo more times then I can count.<br><br>Imprezafreak Eedeeky<br>53rd Journeyman Quad Kiter of Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyiar01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yiar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/26/02 11:40:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=473.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grats</span><hr size=1> Everyone snares themself at one point in time or another.  Ive done it SO many times I've lost track of it already.  I recommend some blue diamond gear for quadding if you can afford it the 8/9 MR and 30 mana that the bracers give you makes for a nice little addition for any set, get a familiar up, and any one of the greater shielding line up for that extra MR, and you will have a lot less of a chance to snare yourself if the critters get close.<br><br>I'm quading SoW'd othmir lately, and when snare is resisted, its nice to have that extra MR to snare them and not myself while they're standing right next to me.  I'm still not too used to seeing the Your target has resisted you Bonds of Force spell, you reisted Bonds of Force in red while I snare them, but if they're not on my tail when I start running, it means I'm still alive. <br><br>A little trick, if you strafe (cntrl-left or cntrl-right) you move faster than snared mobs if your snared yourself.  This will give you a little bit of time to get out of the way and cast gate if you need it.<br><br>Good luck to all you new quadders, its definately a thrill the first few times you get it right.  After that, its a way of life =)<br><br>Yiar<br>59.3 Evoker<br>Resolution -Firiona Vie <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=473.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=473.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.show